Subject: Re: [VB] Filling Body Holes

And if you're *really* AR (ie Dave Mayes, Robert Davis - but not Greg
Noble because he doesn't actually wrench on cars :) ) you'll grind them
from the *inside* as well...

ILoveType2s(-at-)aol.com wrote:
>          Start off by grinding off the paint, leave yourself lots of room.  
> Then clean out the inside of the hole with a drill bit the same size as the 
> hole.  After that bevel the hole with a larger drill bit.   Weld it up, if 
> you keep your heat down their are no need for fences or heat sinks.   The 
> main thing is to no weld so many holes that the heat gets stored up in the 
> metal.  I myself weld one hole on one side and then hop over to the other 
> side, going back and forth between the 2 sides.  After all the holes are no 
> longer holes you'll want to sand blast them.  This is where the little pocket 
> blaster I've mentioned before really shines.  Got the welds blasted?  Its on 
> to the grinding!!  Keep your heat down by making your grinding passes short 
> and sweet.    After some practice you won't need any body fillers, so you 
> might wanna play with some scrap metal first.  Feather, prime, and paint!!

Thom
